1. **Smallest graph piece actually worth stealing**
   The smallest real graph pattern is not the whole `meta3-graph-core` repo, and not the big engine graph modules. It is the tiny packet pipeline inside `/Users/jobs/Desktop/tmp-meta3-engine-test/meta3-graph-core`:
   - `/Users/jobs/Desktop/tmp-meta3-engine-test/meta3-graph-core/src/bin/graph_receipt_ingest.rs`
   - `/Users/jobs/Desktop/tmp-meta3-engine-test/meta3-graph-core/src/bin/graph_utir_ingest.rs`
   - `/Users/jobs/Desktop/tmp-meta3-engine-test/meta3-graph-core/src/bin/graph_merge_packets.rs`

   That trio gives you: ingest structured evidence into a graph-shaped JSON packet, then union packets into one snapshot. No DB, no server, no UI required.

```79:128:/Users/jobs/Desktop/tmp-meta3-engine-test/meta3-graph-core/src/bin/graph_receipt_ingest.rs
fn ingest_event(graph: &mut Graph, event: &ReceiptEvent) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    match event {
        ReceiptEvent::Artifact { path, sha256, bytes, actor, ts } => {
            let id = format!("RECEIPT:artifact:{}", sha256_hex_str(path));
            graph.nodes.push(Node { id: id.clone(), label: Some("artifact".to_string()) });
            graph.nodes.push(Node { id: format!("FILE:{}", path), label: Some("file".to_string()) });
            let content = json!({ "sha256": sha256, "bytes": bytes, "actor": actor, "ts": ts }).to_string();
            graph.links.push(Link {
                source: id,
                target: format!("FILE:{}", path),
                rel: "receipt_targets".to_string(),
                content: Some(content.clone()),
                content_hash: Some(sha256_hex_str(&content)),
            });
        }
        ReceiptEvent::Run { op, ok, ms, args_fingerprint, logs_ref, ts } => {
            let id = format!("RECEIPT:run:{}", sha256_hex_str(&format!("{}:{}:{}", op, ms, ts)));
            graph.nodes.push(Node { id: id.clone(), label: Some("run".to_string()) });
            let content = json!({ "op": op, "ok": ok, "ms": ms, "args_fingerprint": args_fingerprint, "logs_ref": logs_ref, "ts": ts }).to_string();
            graph.links.push(Link {
                source: id,
                target: format!("OP:{}", op),
                rel: "receipt_op".to_string(),
                content: Some(content.clone()),
                content_hash: Some(sha256_hex_str(&content)),
            });
        }
        // ...
    }
    Ok(())
}
